data.content:
The issue is that `Assert.AreEqual` takes `(expected, actual)` — your arguments are reversed. When tests fail, the error message will incorrectly report which value was "expected" vs "actual."

**Fix:** Swap the arguments so the literal expected value comes first:

```csharp
Assert.AreEqual(5, result);
Assert.AreEqual(0, result);
```
